  }), mdx("p", null, "You are working locally without a SSL certificate and in production with certificate,=. The simplest way to work handle both case is to have a configuration that switch depending of if you are in your production server or in your local dev box. Here is two solutions. The first one is well known on Internet but require to have IIS with the rewrite module. This is not a problem with Azure, and even locally it's not a big problem because it can be downloaded from IIS manager console, under Web Platform. But, you won't need that. The first solution is to change the web.release.config to add the redirection on the deployed files only. This is done like this:"), mdx("pre", null, mdx("code", {
